Frontend â€“ UI/UX Guidelines & Functional Requirements
1. Objective

The objective of the frontend is to deliver a smooth, visually attractive, and user-friendly experience while keeping all existing functionalities intact.

All existing functionalities must remain unchanged

Existing background video and animations must NOT be removed or altered

New animations can be added to enhance user experience

2. Functional Consistency

The frontend must behave exactly as defined in the backend flow:

Homepage

Sign In

Create Account

Login

User Dashboard

Admin Dashboard (role-based)

Login, logout, and redirections should work smoothly and seamlessly

Any changes made from the Admin Page must reflect properly on the frontend

3. UI / UX Enhancement Requirements
Attractiveness & Visual Appeal

Improve the overall attractiveness of the website

Focus on:

Clean layouts

Proper spacing

Balanced alignment

Smooth transitions

The website should look modern, premium, and visually engaging.

4. Color Grading

There are no strict color restrictions

You are free to choose any color palette that:

Looks professional

Enhances readability

Improves user engagement

Ensure consistent color grading across all pages, including:

Homepage

Login Page

Sign-Up Page

User Dashboard

Admin Page

The color theme should remain uniform throughout the website.

5. Typography (Fonts)

Use one consistent font family across the entire website

The same font style must be applied on:

All pages

Headings

Buttons

Forms

Navigation menus

Font choice should be:

Clean

Modern

Easy to read

Visually appealing

6. Animations & Transitions
Existing Animations

Do not change or remove:

Background video

Existing animations already implemented

Additional Animations (Allowed)

You may add animations creatively, such as:

Smooth slide-in / slide-out animations

Fade-in effects

Tab opening and closing animations

Hover effects on buttons and cards

Page transition animations

All animations should:

Feel smooth

Not affect performance

Enhance the user experience without distraction

7. Page-Specific UI Focus
Homepage

Visually engaging hero section

Smooth entrance animations

Clear call-to-action buttons (Sign In / Explore)

Login & Sign-Up Pages

Clean and attractive form design

Smooth input focus animations

Proper validation feedback

Consistent styling with the overall theme

User Dashboard

Clear layout

Smooth dropdown animations

Easy navigation between sections

Admin Page

Professional and structured layout

Clear controls for admin operations

Immediate visual reflection of changes on the frontend

8. Performance & Smoothness

The frontend should feel:

Fast

Responsive

Smooth

Animations should not cause lag or delay

Page transitions should be seamless

9. Design Freedom

Developers are encouraged to use their creative freedom

Additional enhancements are welcome as long as:

Core functionality remains unchanged

Existing animations are preserved

Consistent fonts and color grading are maintained

10. Summary

Maintain existing logic and animations

Improve UI/UX and visual appeal

Use consistent fonts and color themes

Add smooth animations where appropriate

Ensure a premium, attractive frontend experienc
